29/12/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- The National Security Council met on Monday (December 28th) for its last session this year to discuss domestic and international political issues, including the fight against terrorism and the government's policy to resolve the Kurdish issue.
Other topics on the agenda were relations between Turkey and the EU, a suspected assassination plot against Deputy Prime Minister Bulent Arinc and recent raids on offices of the General Staff.
"We will continue to fight with determination against terrorism and the atmosphere that cultivates it, which target our nation's integrity and our citizens' unity and peace," the Council said in a statement after the meeting.
(Sabah, Xinhua - 28/12/09)
